# Deploy to:   /etc/aide/aide.conf.d/99-hardening  (append to hardening baseline)
# Apply:       sudo tee -a /etc/aide/aide.conf.d/99-hardening < ~/build-your-infra/modules/dns/self-managed/configs/aide/99-hardening
# Module:      dns
# Requires:    modules/hardening/self-managed/configs/aide/99-hardening applied first
#
# Extends AIDE scope to cover BIND9 config and zone files. Excludes /var/cache/bind
# to avoid false positives from runtime journal and cache writes.
# Parameters modified from baseline:  none — additive only
#
# Note:        Baseline must be regenerated after appending — current BIND9
#              directory state becomes the new trusted snapshot.

# ── DNS — BIND9 config and zone file integrity ────────────────────────────────
/etc/bind        CONTENT_EX
/etc/bind/zones  CONTENT_EX
!/var/cache/bind